{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778377692490,"sessionID":"ses_1f06e0781ffeCBUyFhvIAtgqsy","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ZsBXqALzaZ9jtlL0Al4GTOkj","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__issue_context__.json","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__issue_context__.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"body\": \"All terms introduced in the recently merged PR #3445 (merged despite a failure of the CI check, please don’t do that…) violate taxon constraints.\\r\\n\\r\\nThis is because all those terms have the same following two assertions:\\r\\n\\r\\n> '[in taxon](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162)' some [Astacidea](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_6712)\\r\\n> '[in taxon](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162)' some [Brachyura](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_6752)\\r\\n\\r\\nThis is likely a misunderstanding of the meaning of the '[in taxon](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162)' relation. “X '[in taxon](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162)' some Y” means that **X is specific to the Y taxon**, i.e. X cannot exist in any other taxon that is not Y or a descendant of Y. From that meaning, it follows that a term should never have more than _one_ '[in taxon](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162)' assertion; once a term has been asserted to be '[in taxon](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162)' some Y1, any other assertion '[in taxon](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162)' some Y2 will cause a contradiction, unless Y2 happens to be exactly equivalent to Y1.\\r\\n\\r\\nIf you want to state that an anatomical entity is “known to exist in a given taxon“ but without implying anything about its existence in other taxa, what you need is '[present in taxon](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002175)'.\\r\\n\\r\\nIf you want to state that an anatomical entity exists in a handful of taxa _T1_, _T2_, ... _Tn_, exclusive of all other taxa, then '[in taxon](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162)' is the correct relation but you need to find the closest parental taxon that encompasses all the _T1_, _T2_, ... _Tn_ taxa. In the present case, [Astacidea](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_6712) and [Brachyura](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_6752) are both subtaxa of [Pleocyemata](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_6692), so the ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n3:   \"comments\": [],\n4:   \"title\": \"Newly introduced crab and lobster terms violate taxon constraints\",\n5:   \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3454\"\n6: }\n\n(End of file - total 6 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"body\": \"All terms introduced in the recently merged PR #3445 (merged despite a failure of the CI check, please don’t do that…) violate taxon constraints.\\r\\n\\r\\nThis is because all those terms have the same following two assertions:\\r\\n\\r\\n> '[in taxon](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162)' some [Astacidea](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_6712)\\r\\n> '[in taxon](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162)' some [Brachyura](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_6752)\\r\\n\\r\\nThis is likely a misunderstanding of the meaning of the '[in taxon](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162)' relation. “X '[in taxon](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162)' some Y” means that **X is specific to the Y taxon**, i.e. X cannot exist in any other taxon that is not Y or a descendant of Y. From that meaning, it follows that a term should never have more than _one_ '[in taxon](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162)' assertion; once a term has been asserted to be '[in taxon](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162)' some Y1, any other assertion '[in taxon](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162)' some Y2 will cause a contradiction, unless Y2 happens to be exactly equivalent to Y1.\\r\\n\\r\\nIf you want to state that an anatomical entity is “known to exist in a given taxon“ but without implying anything about its existence in other taxa, what you need is '[present in taxon](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002175)'.\\r\\n\\r\\nIf you want to state that an anatomical entity exists in a handful of taxa _T1_, _T2_, ... _Tn_, exclusive of all other taxa, then '[in taxon](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162)' is the correct relation but you need to find the closest parental taxon that encompasses all the _T1_, _T2_, ... _Tn_ taxa. In the present case, [Astacidea](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_6712) and [Brachyura](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_6752) are both subtaxa of [Pleocyemata](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_6692), so the ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n  \"comments\": [],\n  \"title\": \"Newly introduced crab and lobster terms violate taxon constraints\",\n  \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3454\"\n}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"__issue_context__.json","time":{"start":1778377692479,"end":1778377692488}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02d1b03c1fb279be0169ffe3dc0e908194a681673a36d94551"}},"id":"prt_e0f9213b8001xnE5HDYdEJkCBl","sessionID":"ses_1f06e0781ffeCBUyFhvIAtgqsy","messageID":"msg_e0f920fbe001oX4N2fsJOmM0t7"}}
