nd midgut\" [DOI:10.1016/B0-12-370878-8/00177-4]\n is_a: UBERON:0035014 ! functional part of brain\n relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1909-7004\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6712 ! Astacidea\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6752 ! Brachyura\n+relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6692 ! Pleocyemata\n relationship: part_of UBERON:8910010 ! stomatogastric nerve\n-\n","additions":1,"deletions":3},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910020.obo","relativePath":"terms/UBERON_8910020.obo","type":"update","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910020.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910020.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910020.obo\n@@ -3,8 +3,6 @@\n name: esophageal ganglion (sensu Cancer borealis)\n def: \"Neurons with cell bodies in the esophageal ganglion turn on the gastric mill rhythm and strongly affects the pyloric rhythm.\" [DOI:10.1016/B0-12-370878-8/00177-4]\n is_a: UBERON:0035014 ! functional part of brain\n relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1909-7004\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6712 ! Astacidea\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6752 ! Brachyura\n+relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6692 ! Pleocyemata\n relationship: part_of UBERON:8910000 ! stomatogastric nervous system\n-\n","additions":1,"deletions":3},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910021.obo","relativePath":"terms/UBERON_8910021.obo","type":"update","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910021.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910021.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910021.obo\n@@ -4,8 +4,6 @@\n synonym: \"CG (sensu Cancer borealis)\" EXACT [DOI:10.1016/b978-0-12-809324-5.21166-8]\n def: \"Contains motor fibers that innervate the esophagus. Stimulating the pyloric suppressor neuron alters both pyloric and gastric rhythms but also elicits activity in a third oscillatory circuit located in the commissural ganglia called the esophageal rhythm.\" [DOI:10.1016/b978-0-12-809324-5.21166-8]\n is_a: UBERON:0035014 ! functional part of brain\n relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1909-7004\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6712 ! Astacidea\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6752 ! Brachyura\n+relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6692 ! Pleocyemata\n relationship: part_of UBERON:8910000 ! stomatogastric nervous system\n-\n","additions":1,"deletions":3},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910022.obo","relativePath":"terms/UBERON_8910022.obo","type":"update","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910022.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910022.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910022.obo\n@@ -3,8 +3,6 @@\n name: junction of superior esophageal nerve and stomatogastric nerve (sensu Cancer borealis)\n def: \"The junction between the stomatogastric nerve (STN) and the superior esophageal nerve (SON) shows synaptic structures. Octopamine may be released at this site by projection neurons; its application at this junction induces action potentials in the axons of the modulatory commissural neuron 5 (MCN5) that project from the commissural ganglia to the stomatogastric ganglion (STG).\" [PMID:15306640]\n is_a: UBERON:0035014 ! functional part of brain\n relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1909-7004\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6712 ! Astacidea\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6752 ! Brachyura\n+relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6692 ! Pleocyemata\n relationship: part_of UBERON:8910000 ! stomatogastric nervous system\n-\n","additions":1,"deletions":3},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910023.obo","relativePath":"terms/UBERON_8910023.obo","type":"update","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910023.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910023.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910023.obo\n@@ -4,8 +4,6 @@\n synonym: \"MVN (sensu Cancer borealis)\" EXACT [DOI:10.1016/0010-406X(70)90044-7]\n def: \"Most of the efferent fibers leaving the stomatogastric ganglion and leading to the gastric mill or pyloric stomach muscles run posteriorly in the dorsal median ventricular nerve. This nerve branches bilaterally into the right and left lateral ventricular nerves (LVN) which go to their respective sides of the stomach.\" [DOI:10.1016/0010-406X(70)90044-7]\n is_a: UBERON:0035014 ! functional part of brain\n relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1909-7004\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6712 ! Astacidea\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6752 ! Brachyura\n+relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6692 ! Pleocyemata\n relationship: part_of UBERON:8910000 ! stomatogastric nervous system\n-\n","additions":1,"deletions":3}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nM terms/UBERON_8910001.obo\nM terms/UBERON_8910010.obo\nM terms/UBERON_8910011.obo\nM terms/UBERON_8910012.obo\nM terms/UBERON_8910013.obo\nM terms/UBERON_8910014.obo\nM terms/UBERON_8910015.obo\nM terms/UBERON_8910016.obo\nM terms/UBERON_8910017.obo\nM terms/UBERON_8910018.obo\nM terms/UBERON_8910019.obo\nM terms/UBERON_8910020.obo\nM terms/UBERON_8910021.obo\nM terms/UBERON_8910022.obo\nM terms/UBERON_8910023.obo","time":{"start":1778377739183,"end":17783777392